Hi Alex,

maybe I can help, p and span are two different html elements. usually, the span is embedded in the P element to allow to manipulation of a specific portion of the P element. My example is below:

HTML:

<p>P element text before the span element <span class="span_manipulation"> Span element </span>Text after span element </p>

CSS:

/* the "." = class in css and allows us to call the span    class element above to manipulate the text inside it based on the following css rule. */


.span_manipulation {                                          
color: red;
text-transform: uppercase;
font-weight: bolder;
}

